Package grafioschtrader.platformimport

Class TemplateConfiguration

java.lang.Object
grafioschtrader.platformimport.TemplateConfiguration
Direct Known Subclasses:
TemplateConfigurationAndStateCsv, TemplateConfigurationPDFasTXT
public abstract class TemplateConfiguration extends Object
Abstract base class for configuring and parsing transaction import templates from PDF or CSV text sources.

This class handles configuration parsing, number formatting, date/time patterns, transaction type mappings, and locale-specific formatting rules.

Template Structure

Templates contain property definitions followed by a configuration section marked by the [END] delimiter.

Configuration Options

Configuration keys supported in the [END] section:

  • dateFormat - Date format pattern (e.g., "yyyy-MM-dd")
  • timeFormat - Time format pattern (e.g., "HH:mm:ss")
  • transType - Transaction type mappings: "TRANSACTION_TYPE|word1,word2,word3"
  • overRuleSeparators - Custom number separators (e.g., "Allinvalid input: '<''|.>")
  • otherFlagOptions - Feature flags separated by "|"
  • ignoreTaxOnDivInt - Transaction type for tax exemption

This class is not thread-safe. Parsing errors are collected in a DataViolationException.

    • readTemplateProperties

      protected abstract void readTemplateProperties(String[] templateLines, int startRowConfig, DataViolationException dataViolationException)

      Parameters:
      templateLines - Array of template lines, already normalized
      startRowConfig - Index where the configuration section begins (after [END])
      dataViolationException - Exception object to collect any validation errors

      Throws:
      DataViolationException - if any validation errors are found during parsing

    • parseTemplat

      protected DataViolationException parseTemplat(boolean forSaving)
      Parses an import template for financial transaction documents and extracts field mappings and configuration. Handles the complete template processing workflow: normalization, configuration parsing, field mapping setup, and validation.
      Parameters:
      forSaving - Whether this parsing is for template validation before saving
      Returns:
      A DataViolationException containing any validation errors found (may be empty)
